    "(15)One can now move two topological operators across sequentially, or first fuse them and then move them across, leading to the consistency conditiong 2 • (g 1 • O) = (g 2 g 1) • O.",
    "(16)Moreover, the topological operator corresponding to 1 ∈ G (0) is the identity operator, which clearly has the action 1:O -→ O.",
